<h3>About OpenSplitTime</h3>
<hr>
<p>
  OpenSplitTime is developed and maintained by endurance athletes for endurance athletes. If you are a race director,
  feel free to upload your data! Instructions for creating a new event (including formatting your Excel or CSV data
  file) may be found <%= link_to "here", getting_started_path %>.
</p>
<p>
  Your data will always be freely available to you and to your race participants. This site is supported exclusively by
  user
  donations. Sensitive data is carefully controlled and restricted to authorized viewers.
</p>
<p>
  The site is owned by OpenSplitTime Company, a Colorado nonprofit corporation. If you find the website useful,
  motivating, entertaining, or strangely beautiful, please consider making a
  small <%= link_to "donation", donations_path %> to help us keep the doors
  open. OpenSplitTime Company is registered with the U.S. Internal Revenue Service as a 501(c)(3) charitable
  organization. Your donations may be tax deductible.
</p>
<p>
  Our software is open source. If you have a suggestion for the site, or you are a software engineer and would like to
  help with development, or if you are a race director or data geek and would like to be an alpha tester,
  please <%= mail_to "mark.oveson@gmail.com", "contact Mark" %> and we'll work something out.
</p>
